<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href=" stylesheets.courses.css" />
    <title>Course Outline</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <%- include("_nav.ejs") %>
      <h1>Course Outline</h1>
      <p>
        This course is designed to provide comprehensive knowledge and practical
        skills in building secure and efficient login systems for web
        applications. Participants will learn the fundamentals of user
        authentication, session management, and data security, as well as
        advanced techniques for handling various login scenarios and
        implementing best practices.
      </p>

      <h2>Course Outline</h2>
      <ul>
        <h1>Introduction to Authentication</h1>
        <p>
          <li>
            Understanding the importance of authentication in web applications
          </li>
          <li>Differentiating between authentication and authorization</li>
          <li>
            Overview of common authentication methods (e.g., password-based,
            token-based)
          </li>
        </p>

        <h1>User Registration and Account Creation</h1>
        <p>
          <li>Designing user registration forms and workflows</li>
          <li>
            Implementing secure password storage and encryption techniques
          </li>
          <li>Validating user input and handling registration errors</li>
        </p>

        <h1>Login Mechanisms</h1>
        <p>
          <li>
            Implementing login forms with username/password authentication
          </li>
          <li>
            Exploring alternative login methods (e.g., social login,
            multi-factor authentication)
          </li>
          <li>
            Handling login failures and implementing account lockout mechanisms
          </li>
        </p>

        <h1>Session Management</h1>
        <p>
          <li>
            Understanding session-based authentication and state management
          </li>
          <li>
            Implementing secure session handling techniques (e.g., session
            tokens, cookies)
          </li>
          <li>
            Managing session expiration, renewal, and logout functionality
          </li>
        </p>

        <h1>Data Security and Protection</h1>
        <p>
          <li>
            Protecting sensitive user data during transmission and storage
          </li>
          <li>
            Implementing HTTPS and SSL/TLS encryption for secure communication
          </li>
          <li>
            Preventing common security vulnerabilities (e.g., SQL injection,
            cross-site scripting)
          </li>
        </p>

        <h1>Advanced Topics and Best Practices</h1>
        <p>
          <li>
            Exploring advanced authentication features (e.g., password reset,
            remember me functionality)
          </li>
          <li>
            Implementing role-based access control (RBAC) and permission
            management
          </li>
          <li>
            Reviewing industry best practices and security standards for login
            systems
          </li>
        </p>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Prerequisites: Basic knowledge of web development (HTML, CSS,
        JavaScript) and familiarity with server-side programming languages
        (e.g., Python, PHP, Node.js) is recommended.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
